It seems that you are trying to output the entire hashmap object. In order to correctly display the outcome with the highest probability, you need to find the key with the highest value in the hashmap and return that key as the result. Let me correct the function for you.

```javascript
function PredictCirrhosisOutcomes(N_Days, Drug, Age, Sex, Ascites, Hepatomegaly, Spiders, Edema, Bilirubin, Cholesterol, Albumin, Copper, Alk_Phos, SGOT, Tryglicerides, Platelets, Prothrombin, Stage) {
  // Your prediction code here
  // Calculate probabilities for each outcome (C, CL, D)
  // Return the outcome with the highest probability
  let probabilities = {
    C: 0.5,
    CL: 0.3,
    D: 0.2
  };

  let maxProb = Math.max(probabilities.C, probabilities.CL, probabilities.D);

  if (maxProb === probabilities.C) {
    return "C";
  } else if (maxProb === probabilities.CL) {
    return "CL";
  } else {
    return "D";
  }
}
```
Now when you run the function with the same input, it will return "C" as the outcome.
